-- Union Properties Nears Deal on Dubai Ritz-Carlton Sale, National Reports
-- Anthony DiPaola
-- 2010-07-26T04:20:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/union-properties-nears-deal-on-dubai-ritz-carlton-sale-national-reports.html

          
          
             Union Properties PJSC  may agree this
week to sell the Ritz-Carlton hotel development in Dubai for
almost its asking price of 1.5 billion dirhams ($410 million),
 The National  reported, citing Chairman  Khalid bin Kalban .  
 The company is discussing terms with a bidder from the
United Arab Emirates and a potential buyer from Saudi Arabia is
also in the running, the newspaper said.  
 Proceeds from the sale of the building in the  Dubai
International Financial Center  will go to other projects, The
National cited bin Kalban as saying.  
 To contact the reporters on this story:
